title: Another North Shore crown for Homestead Higlanders
text:
Another North Shore crown for Homestead Higlanders By Mark Stewart of the Journal Sentinel Oct. 16, 2015 11:48 p.m. (0) Comments 
Make that 15 straight for Homestead. 
The Highlanders defeated Cedarburg, 35-0, Friday in Mequon to win its 15th straight North Shore Conference football title. They shared the title with Whitefish Bay, which clinched its share with a 42-21 victory over Grafton. 
Cedarburg also entered the final week tied for the league lead. Homestead (7-2, 6-1 North Shore) scored its fourth shutout of the season and held the Bulldogs (7-2, 5-2) to 140 total yards. 
Senior running back Matt Winters finished with 146 yards and a touchdown in 29 carries for Homestead. Junior quarterback Eric Zoeller completed 5 of 6 passes for 68 yards and two touchdowns. Zoeller also ran for a 23-yard score and finished second on the team with 52 rushing yards in nine carries.
